-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/grameenphone-s-half-year-profit-rises-40-on-user-additions.html
Grameenphone Ltd. (GRAM) , the Bangladesh
unit of Telenor ASA, said net profit rose 40 percent in the six
months through June boosted by user additions and sales of
handsets.  Net income for the first half of 2011 rose to 6.77 billion
taka ($90.8 million), or 5.01 taka a share, from 4.83 billion
taka, or 3.58 taka, in the same period a year earlier,
Grameenphone said in a statement.  The Dhaka-based company increased its retail network by
264,000 shops to reach rural areas and added 3.9 million new
customers in the six months, according to the statement.
Grameenphone had 33.8 million customers, with a 44.3 percent
share of the Bangladesh market, at the end of June.  The shares rose 10 percent to 195 taka each at the 3 p.m.
close on the Dhaka Stock Exchange. The benchmark General Index
climbed 101 points, or 1.6 percent, to 6,587.58.  With assistance from Malavika Sharma in  New Delhi . Editor:  To contact the reporter on this story:
